cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically deals with word representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses techniques for building word vectors, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also proposes a model that discriminates between different senses of polysemic words, which involves classification and could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed model, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
